subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
. 102 (96–104) µm long, 68 (69–72) µm wide. Anterior and posterior additional setae, and seta 
m4
present; anterior and posterior sensilla present (
Fig. 5A
); median subposterior seta length, 8 (7–9) µm, 1.2 times longer than median posterior seta, 7 (7) µm; a pair of rudimentary sensilla posterior to pseudoculus rudimentary. Labral setae present (
Fig. 5B
). Rostral seta length 13 (11–13) µm, longer than subrostral seta, 11 (10–12) µm, (
Fig. 5B
). On maxillary palpus (
Fig. 5C
) dorsal sensillum (
md
), 6 (5–6) µm, longer than lateral sensillum (
ml
), 4 (4–5) µm. On galea (
Fig. 5D
), all digits similar in shape and length. Mandible with two teeth (
Fig. 5E
). Clypeal apodeme distinct (
Fig. 5A, B
). Pseudoculus with a weak central mark (
Fig. 5F
), 9 (8–11) µm long, PR=12 (10–13).

